A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Education – Phone–Free Schools Pilot Program – Establishment
3 FOR the purpose of establishing the Phone–Free Schools Pilot Program; requiring certain
4 local school systems to develop and implement a policy that prohibits student cell
5 phone use during the school day, subject to certain exceptions; and generally relating
6 to the Phone–Free Schools Pilot Program.
7 BY adding to
8 Article – Education
9 Section 7–136
10 Annotated Code of Maryland
11 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
12 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
13 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
14 Article – Education
15 7–136.
16 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
17 INDICATED.
18 (2) “ELIGIBLE LOCAL SCHOOL SYSTEM” MEANS:
19 (I) THE CARROLL COUNTY PUBLIC SCHOOL SYSTEM; AND
20 (II) THE MONTGOMERY COUNTY PUBLIC SCHOOL SYSTEM.
21 (3) “INSTRUCTIONAL TIME” MEANS ANY TIME DURING THE SCHOOL
22 DAY, EXCEPT A STUDENT’S LUNCH PERIOD.

2 SENATE BILL 29
1 (4) “PILOT PROGRAM” MEANS THE PHONE–FREE SCHOOLS PILOT
2 PROGRAM.
3 (B) THERE IS A PHONE–FREE SCHOOLS PILOT PROGRAM.
4 (C) THE PURPOSE OF THE PILOT PROGRAM IS TO COLLECT DATA TO
5 DETERMINE THE EFFECT OF LOCAL SCHOOL SYSTEM POLICIES THAT LIMIT STUDENT
6 USE OF CELL PHONES DURING THE SCHOOL DAY ON:
7 (1) ACADEMIC ACHIEVEMENT;
8 (2) STUDENT CLASSROOM ENGAGEMENT;
9 (3) STUDENT SOCIAL INTERACTIONS; AND
10 (4) STUDENT BEHAVIOR AND DISCIPLINE.
11 (D) (1) EACH ELIGIBLE LOCAL SCHOOL SYSTEM SHALL SELECT ONE
12 MIDDLE SCHOOL AND ONE HIGH SCHOOL IN THE COUNTY TO PARTICIPATE IN THE
13 PILOT PROGRAM.
14 (2) EACH ELIGIBLE LOCAL SCHOOL SYSTEM SHALL:
15 (I) DEVELOP AND IMPLEMENT A POLICY THAT PROHIBITS
16 STUDENT CELL PHONE USE DURING INSTRUCTIONAL TIME; AND
17 (II) ESTABLISH PROCEDURES TO ENFORCE THE POLICY,
18 INCLUDING APPROPRIATE DISCIPLINARY MEASURES FOR VIOLATIONS.
19 (3) THE POLICY DEVELOPED UNDER THIS SUBSECTION MAY NOT
20 PROHIBIT A STUDENT FROM USING A CELL PHONE:
21 (I) FOR ANY PURPOSE DOCUMENTED IN THE STUDENT’S
22 INDIVIDUALIZED EDUCATION PROGRAM OR SECTION 504 PLAN;
23 (II) TO MONITOR OR ADDRESS A STUDENT’S DOCUMENTED
24 HEALTH ISSUE; OR
25 (III) WHEN DIRECTED BY AN EDUCATOR OR ADMINISTRATOR
26 FOR EDUCATIONAL PURPOSES.
27 (E) (1) EACH ELIGIBLE LOCAL SCHOOL SYSTEM SHALL COLLECT DATA
28 REGARDING THE STUDENT CELL PHONE USE POLICY, INCLUDING:

SENATE BILL 29 3
1 (I) ACADEMIC ACHIEVEMENT OF STUDENTS IN THE SCHOOL;
2 (II) STUDENT CLASSROOM ENGAGEMENT;
3 (III) STUDENT SOCIAL INTERACTIONS, INCLUDING BULLYING,
4 CYBERBULLYING, AND HARASSMENT;
5 (IV) STUDENT BEHAVIOR AND DISCIPLINE;
6 (V) ENFORCEMENT CHALLENGES;
7 (VI) STUDENT FEEDBACK ON THE POLICY;
8 (VII) TEACHER FEEDBACK ON THE POLICY; AND
9 (VIII) PARENT OR GUARDIAN FEEDBACK ON THE POLICY.
10 (2) ON OR BEFORE SEPTEMBER 1, 2026, EACH ELIGIBLE LOCAL
11 SCHOOL SYSTEM SHALL SUBMIT A REPORT BASED ON THE DATA COLLECTED UNDER
12 PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION TO THE DEPARTMENT AND, IN ACCORDANCE
13 WITH § 2–1257 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE, THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY
14 ON THE EFFECTIVENESS OF THE PILOT PROGRAM.
15 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
16 1, 2025.

